<dl id="n53034u"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53034u">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53034u"> 34(u)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> purim, ~ <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53034u"><li>FW 245.36 </li><li><a href="../../flex/ke/lexke.htm#n53034u">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/ke/l39ke.htm#n53034u">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53034u">MS BL 47477-174</ms> </li><li>JJA 51:251 <a name="kad8" href="../../ff/fdra/kda.htm#ked7">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/ke/ked7.htm#n53034u">Draft: II.1&sect;5.7</a> </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: The Feast of Purim (from the Assyrian word for &lsquo;lot&rsquo; &mdash; puru) is a Spring celebration. It marks the massacre of the Jews by the Persians in 473 BC as related in the Book of Esther (9.26ff) and of their deliverance from Haman&apos;s seeking to exterminate them (in an early Final Solution). </mm> </dd></dl>
